<br>
Don't suggest CS, because that zone is too crowded for quadding.<br>
<br>
Are Suits of Sentient Armor in WL good at my level? <p>Zwobu &lt;Trade&nbsp;Foundation&gt; Innoruuk<br><img src="http://members.home.net/zwobu/zwobu.jpeg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvortextwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VortexTwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 9:36:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just turned 51 and desperate to test out PoF</span><hr size=1> Sorry if I'm stealing all your wyverns Z. May I suggest some loot quading?<br>
<br>
Hill Giants in Lake Rathe really don't like PoF. :P <p><p align="center"><img src="http://www.bigjaco.com/SG/eq_screenies/vort_sig53.jpg"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umcdermit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mcdermit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 9:53:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just turned 51 and desperate to test out PoF</span><hr size=1> Hehe, it's not that the Wyverns aren't there. There's just not enough space to round them up and get far enough away to Atols without passing by someone else. I don't like to quad near other people because of the risk, however slight, of training them. Plus, I have several mules full up on Wyvern Hides; time to hunt something else.<br>
<br>
Mmmm, looot. Even better. It'll give my friends a chance to catch up to me instead of completely leaving them in the dust ;)<br>
<br>
HGs in Lake Rath or Rathe Mtns? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 11:27:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just turned 51 and desperate to test out PoF</span><hr size=1> FYI -<br>
<br>
while it is impolite, you can pull agro'd wyverns over someone and they will ignore them. Happened to me, I about crapped myself when I turned around to see a wall of wyverns running at me!<br>
<br>
I do this to my friends for fun the first time they come to CS... LOL <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 48th Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i><p>
<span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Moordian Killbringer<br>Warrior of 25 Battle Scars</b><br><i>Dwarven LaMachine of Death</i><br><span style="font-size: 12px; font-famliy: arial">proud member of Infinity Watch - Terris-Thule server</span></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umcdermit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mcdermit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 12:22:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just turned 51 and desperate to test out PoF</span><hr size=1> ...unless that person is fighting a Wyvern when you pass by, in which case they will aggro, and return for that person if you die or gate or just get to far away from the mobs. I've been aggro'd by both Wyverns and Drakes that were kited past me while I was fighting a Wyvern.<br>
<br>
I was looking in Illa's Beastiary at the Suits in WL, and they look soloable, but not quite quadable at 51. Anyone have any experience with these? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umcdermit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mcdermit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/01 6:37:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just turned 51 and desperate to test out PoF</span><hr size=1> OK, suits in WL are no-go for quadding. Based on my rough calculations they have about 10k HP, which means you'd need to be 60 and bust out Ice Spear to solo them.<br>
<br>
I'll post more accurate numbers after I drag Vortextwin to WL tonight to see if we can take one together ;)<br>
<br>
EDIT: OK, I took a closer look at my logs, and the suits only have about 7k HP. Soloing them might be an option in your high 50's. A Vort (lvl 53) and I (lvl 51) were able to take them down together halfway well, but one of them ran us both oom and had significant health left (how long did that one take us, Vort? 20 minutes?). These are definately a group effort, and they don't look like they'll ever make for good quadding. Also, very little loot. No coin, and gems/armor is not all that common. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umcdermit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mcdermit</A> at: 6/21/01 6:45:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufuryfingerz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Furyfingerz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/21/01 7:47:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just turned 51 and desperate to test out PoF</span><hr size=1> I'm also interested in Quadding with PoF and not in Velious.<br>
I did SF's in OOT last night, but took all my mana with no resists. Too dangerous IMHO. I hear BW is good but finding blues together for quadding may be the hard part. I'm going to try near the hornets nest tonight and will report back.<br>
<br>
Any other suggestions for level 51 quadding? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uqaman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/21/01 9:55:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just turned 51 and desperate to test out PoF</span><hr size=1> Burning woods is good for quadding at 51. All the monkeys, skels, and hornets all run at the same speed and are easy to quad. Just stay away from the higher level ones at 51 to make it easier. You can take giants, but they go into run mode at a certain point (the others don't) which makes them a pain because you have to finish them off singly. Stay away from Sarnarks because they tend to be SoWed.<br>
<br>
EJ is also decent at 51 if you are good at running around and pulling. <p>Qaman<BR>
Sorcerer<BR>
Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwolandgrauensturm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Woland Grauensturm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/01 1:17:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just turned 51 and desperate to test out PoF</span><hr size=1> <br>
